>> title: Mediterranean Chicken Skewers
>> servings: 4
>> prep time: 20 minutes
>> cook time: 25 minutes

@{For cucumber yogurt sauce:}1. In a bowl, whisk together @extra virgin olive oil{0.25%cup}, @lemon juice{1%tbsp}, @garlic{4%cloves}, @oregano{2%tsp}, @thyme{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper to make marinade.

@{For cucumber yogurt sauce:}2. Cut chicken into 1.5-inch cubes and add to marinade. Let marinate for at least 30 minutes or up to 2 hours.

@{For cucumber yogurt sauce:}3. If using wooden @Wooden or metal skewers{}, soak them in water for 30 minutes.

@{For cucumber yogurt sauce:}4. Thread chicken onto @Wooden or metal skewers{}, leaving small spaces between pieces.

@{For cucumber yogurt sauce:}5. Preheat grill or grill pan to medium-high heat.

@{For cucumber yogurt sauce:}6. Cook @Wooden or metal skewers{} for 12-15 minutes, turning every 3-4 minutes, until chicken is cooked through (internal temp 165Â°F).

@{For cucumber yogurt sauce:}7. Meanwhile, prepare @prepared rice pilaf{2%cups} according to package directions, adding diced vegetables if desired.

@{For cucumber yogurt sauce:}8. For @cucumber{1} yogurt sauce: Mix @plain Greek yogurt{1%cup}, cucumber, @garlic{4%cloves}, @lemon juice{1%tbsp}, @dill{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

@{For cucumber yogurt sauce:}9. Serve @Wooden or metal skewers{} over @prepared rice pilaf{2%cups} with @cucumber{1} @plain Greek yogurt{1%cup} sauce on the side.

@{For cucumber yogurt sauce:}10. Kids love eating food off sticks - let them help thread the chicken onto @Wooden or metal skewers{}!

-- Category: Mediterranean
-- Cholesterol benefits: Lean chicken provides high-quality protein with minimal saturated fat. The marinade uses olive oil instead of butter-based marinades. Greek yogurt in the sauce provides probiotics and protein. Kids love the interactive nature of eating from skewers, making this a fun family meal.
